<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11121i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11121i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11121i"> 121(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> MacDonald / je mentis</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Le Retour de Louis XVIII</b> &ldquo;Les mar&eacute;chaux <mark>Macdonald</mark>, Ney, Moncey, Serrurier, Brune, le prince de Neuch&acirc;tel, tous les g&eacute;n&eacute;raux, toutes les personnes pr&eacute;sentes, ont obtenu pareillement du roi les paroles les plus affectueuses. Telle est en France la force du souverain l&eacute;gitime, cette magie attach&eacute;e au nom du roi. Un homme arrive seul de l&apos;exil, d&eacute;pouill&eacute; de tout, sans suite, sans gardes, sans richesses; il n&apos;a rien &agrave; donner, presque rien &agrave; promettre. Il descend de sa voiture, appuy&eacute; sur le bras d&apos;une jeune femme; il se montre &agrave; des capitaines qui ne l&apos;ont jamais vu, &agrave; des grenadiers qui savent &agrave; peine son nom. Quel est cet homme? c&apos;est le roi! Tout le monde tombe &agrave; ses pieds.&rdquo; / Ce que je disais l&agrave; des guerriers, dans le but que je me proposais d&apos;atteindre, &eacute;tait vrai quant aux chefs; mais <mark>je mentais</mark> &agrave; l&apos;&eacute;gard des soldats. <br><font color="green">[The Return of Louis XVIII: &ldquo;The Field-Marshals Macdonald, Ney, Moncey, Serrurier, Brune, the Prince of Neuch&acirc;tel, all the generals and all attending persons were addressed alike by the king in the most loving terms. Such in France is the might of the legitimate sovereign, the magic attached to the king&apos;s name. A man comes back from exile despoiled of everything, with no suite, no guard, no wealth; he has nothing to give, as good as nothing to promise. He steps down from his coach, leaning over a young lady&apos;s arm; he shows himself to captains that have never seen him, to grenadiers that hardly know his name. Who is this man? He is the king! Everyone falls to their knees before him.&rdquo; / What I said to the warriors, for the end that I proposed to reach, was true for the leaders; but I lied as regards the soldiers.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 100</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
